mp;topicid=MH3D6EB198&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Family Sharing set up</a>, you can turn on Ask to Buy so that you&#x2019;re asked to approve any purchases for certain family members.</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openApp?bundleId=com.apple.iBooksX\" class=\"URL\">Open iBooks for me</a></p><div id=\"ibks11b7c449\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-ibks11b7c449\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Control access to the iBooks Store and explicit content</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-ibks11b7c449\"><ol><li><p>Choose iBooks&#xA0;&gt; Preferences, then click Parental.</p></li><li><p>Click the lock icon <span class=\"NoBreak\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5A5401DF0946220B614CDC9D/5A5401E00946220B614CDCA4/en_US/314aad0915d1135d3070820482bc2166.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_LockSysPrefs_osx.png\">,</span> then enter the administrator name and password for your computer.</p></li><li><p>Select options.</p><ul><li><p><em>Disable the iBooks Store: </em>Anyone using your Mac can view your library, but can&#x2019;t open the iBooks Store.</p></li><li><p><em>Restrict books with explicit content: </em> Anyone using your Mac can see the titles of explicit books in your library or the iBooks Store, but can&#x2019;t access the books or see their descriptions.</p></li></ul></li><li><p>When you&#x2019;re done, click the lock again.</p></li></ol></div></div><div id=\"apd204e2bae50014\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-apd204e2bae50014\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Turn on Ask to Buy</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-apd204e2bae50014\"><p>Ask to Buy is on by default for children under 13, and can be turned on for family members under 18. (Specific age limits may vary in different countries or regions.) For more information, see <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=mac-help&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH3D6EB198&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Set up Family Sharing</a>.</p><ol><li><p>Choose Apple menu&#xA0;&gt; System Preferences, then click iCloud. </p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.preferences.icloud\" class=\"URL\">Open iCloud preferences for me</a></p></li><li><p>Click Manage Family.</p></li><li><p>Select the family member on the left, then turn on Ask to Buy on the right.</p></li></ol></div></div><p>You can also control access to the iBooks Store and explicit content using Parental Controls preferences. For more information, see <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=mac-help&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2913&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Parental Controls Stores preferences</a>.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?product=mac-help&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLC2B37692&amp;type=ddm\" class=\"URL\">Share purchases with your family</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=ibooks&amp;vanityname=hide-purchased-books&amp;version=1.11&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=IBKSA4E88313&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.13\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Hide purchased books</a></div></body>"}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS High Sierra","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"7864"},{"key":"Unarchived","name":"Unarchived","englishName":"Unarchived","displayName":"Unarchived","articleCount":"10186"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"macOS High Sierra","name":"macOS High Sierra","englishName":"macOS High Sierra","displayN